Log into GitHub Enterprise:

As an admin, go to GitHub Enterprise Settings for your organization.
Enable SAML SSO:

Navigate to Settings > Organization security > Single sign-on.
Click Configure SAML SSO.
Upload the Federation Metadata XML:

Upload the Federation Metadata XML that you downloaded from Azure AD in the previous step.
Configure Required Information:

Ensure the following fields are correctly filled out (these should match the SAML configuration from Azure AD):
SSO URL: This is the Azure AD Login URL.
Entity ID: https://github.com.
SAML certificate: The certificate from Azure AD.
Test and Save:

Test the SSO setup by clicking Test SSO in GitHub to ensure everything works as expected.
Once tested, click Save to finalize the configuration.
